.TH "ring_buffer_record_disable" 9 "ring_buffer_record_disable" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ring_buffer_record_disable \- stop all writes into the buffer
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" ring_buffer_record_disable
.BI "(struct trace_buffer *buffer "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "buffer" 12
The ring buffer to stop writes to.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This prevents all writes to the buffer. Any attempt to write
to the buffer after this will fail and return NULL.

The caller should call \fBsynchronize_rcu\fP after this.
